In total, there are 6 rapids between Khartoum and Aswan. The first of them, the closest to the mouth, is located in the Aswan region, north of the Aswan Dam. from the Sudanese-Egyptian border) the rapids were a serious obstacle to continuous navigation. In the region of the rapids, year-round navigation was possible only by boat. For permanent navigation, the sections between Khartoum and Juba, Aswan and Cairo, Cairo and the mouth of the Nile were used.